      • addLanguage

        void addLanguage​(net.minecraft.client.resource.language.LanguageDefinition def)
        Add a custom language. Translations must be added separately with addTranslations(net.minecraft.util.Identifier, com.swordglowsblue.artifice.api.util.Processor<com.swordglowsblue.artifice.api.builder.assets.TranslationBuilder>).
        Parameters:

      • addLanguage

        void addLanguage​(java.lang.String code,
                 java.lang.String region,
                 java.lang.String name,
                 boolean rtl)
        Add a custom language. Translations must be added separately with addTranslations(net.minecraft.util.Identifier, com.swordglowsblue.artifice.api.util.Processor<com.swordglowsblue.artifice.api.builder.assets.TranslationBuilder>).
        Parameters:
        code - The language code for the custom language (i.e. en_us). Must be all lowercase alphanum / underscores.
        region - The name of the language region (i.e. United States).
        name - The name of the language (i.e. English).
        rtl - Whether the language is written right-to-left instead of left-to-right.
